{"ts":"2026-06-27T11:17:49.413Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_end","contentType":"reasoning","reasoning":"**Creating API Endpoints**\n\nI've got the `lib/api-auth.ts` file created, and I'm ready to move on. Next up, I will implement the endpoints. I'm planning to create three API endpoints: `app/api/v1/auth/login/route.ts`, `app/api/v1/auth/me/route.ts`, and `app/api/v1/auth/logout/route.ts`. Let's do this!\n\n\n**Designing Login Endpoint**\n\nI'm deep in the `/api/v1/auth/login/route.ts` file now. I've ensured it only handles `POST` requests and started the initial setup. I'm focusing on crafting a robust error-handling strategy, especially for invalid credentials and inactive users. I've just started outlining the request body parsing and verification with the use of helper functions. I'll need to remember to return the JWT access token and user info as per the spec.\n\n\n**Implementing Error Handling**\n\nI've just added detailed error handling to the login endpoint, explicitly addressing cases with missing or invalid credentials, as well as inactive users. I have considered returning specific error responses based on different failure scenarios, and included informative error messages. I'm taking care to normalize the email and checking the user status. Now I will move to password verification.\n\n\n"}}
{"ts":"2026-06-27T11:17:49.415Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"tool","toolName":"editor","toolCallId":"yby6j4in","input":{"path":"/Users/ayushbansal/Documents/GitHub/hirezapp_landing_page/app/api/v1/auth/login/route.ts","new_text":"import { NextResponse } from \"next/server\";\nimport { API_MOCK_USERS, verifyUserPassword, signJwt } from \"@/lib/api-auth\";\n\nexport const runtime = \"nodejs\";\n\nexport async function POST(req: Request) {\n  try {\n    const body = await req.json().catch(() => null);\n    if (!body) {\n      return NextResponse.json(\n        { success: false, error: \"Bad Request\", message: \"Invalid JSON body provided.\" },\n        { status: 400 }\n      );\n    }\n\n    const { email, password } = body;\n\n    if (!email || !password) {\n      return NextResponse.json(\n        { success: false, error: \"Bad Request\", message: \"Email and password are required fields.\" },\n        { status: 400 }\n      );\n    }\n\n    const normalizedEmail = email.toLowerCase().trim();\n    const user = API_MOCK_USERS[normalizedEmail];\n\n    if (!user) {\n      return NextResponse.json(\n        { success: false, error: \"Unauthorized\", message: \"Invalid credentials provided.\" },\n        { status: 401 }\n      );\n    }\n\n    if (user.status === \"inactive\") {\n      return NextResponse.json(\n        { success: false, error: \"Forbidden\", message: \"This account is inactive. Please contact your platform administrator.\" },\n        { status: 403 }\n      );\n    }\n\n    const isValidPassword = verifyUserPassword(normalizedEmail, password);\n    if (!isValidPassword) {\n      return NextResponse.json(\n        { success: false, error: \"Unauthorized\", message: \"Invalid credentials provided.\" },\n        { status: 401 }\n      );\n    }\n\n    const tokenPayload = {\n      sub: user.id,\n      email: user.email,\n      role: user.role,\n      name: user.name,\n      clearance: user.clearance,\n    };\n\n    const accessToken = signJwt(tokenPayload);\n\n    // Exclude passwordHash from user info returned\n    const { passwordHash, ...userResponse } = user;\n\n    return NextResponse.json(\n      {\n        success: true,\n        accessToken,\n        tokenType: \"Bearer\",\n        expiresIn: 3600,\n        user: userResponse,\n      },\n      { status: 200 }\n    );\n  } catch (error: any) {\n    console.error(\"Auth login error:\", error);\n    return NextResponse.json(\n      { success: false, error: \"Internal Server Error\", message: \"An unexpected error occurred during authentication.\" },\n      { status: 500 }\n    );\n  }\n}\n"}}}
